00:18:22.950 --> 00:18:23.950
the law?

00:18:23.950 --> 00:18:27.370
&gt;&gt;Micah Sifry: Well, I look I mean I think
what's interesting about the time that we

00:18:27.370 --> 00:18:35.490
live in is that the ability to share, uh,
information that matters is now in everybody's

00:18:35.490 --> 00:18:41.330
hands. Um, you know, we're only a few years
into this phenomenon of everyone carrying

00:18:41.330 --> 00:18:48.120
a networked printing press in their pocket.
Um, so the the old way of doing things, which

00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:53.760
is still dominant, which is about control
of information and secrecy and lack of accountability,

00:18:53.760 --> 00:19:01.299
is being fundamentally threatened. Um, I mean
what Google does is fundamentally threatening

00:19:01.299 --> 00:19:10.360
to the ability of people to, uh, you know,
to lie in your face. Right? Because if if

00:19:10.360 --> 00:19:16.010
I'm talking to my member of congress at a,
in a public hearing and they, public event

00:19:16.010 --> 00:19:19.480
or something, and they say something and I'm
like that's exactly the opposite of what you

00:19:19.480 --> 00:19:25.670
said two years ago. I can actually look it
up, pull it up, play it back to them. Um,

00:19:25.670 --> 00:19:31.890
what what happens after that? Right? That's
the moment that we're in now, um, and my argument

00:19:31.890 --> 00:19:38.210
is is that we're we're in this like a paradigm
shift. It's gonna be messy and upsetting to

00:19:38.210 --> 00:19:43.290
the people in power. And they're gonna say
things like, "You can't have that information.

00:19:43.290 --> 00:19:51.010
You stole it." Right? Um, but we now have
it. Uh, not every, in not every case because

00:19:51.010 --> 00:19:54.910
somebody leaked it either. Right? It's just
because it's been well organized and put at

00:19:54.910 --> 00:20:01.500
our fingertips. Um, and I think that's gonna
be really really disruptive to the current

00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:06.710
generation and profoundly positive for the
next generation. 'Cause I also think we're

00:20:06.710 --> 00:20:12.630
gonna get new leaders, we're gonna get new
folks in all kinds of positions of authority

00:20:12.630 --> 00:20:18.460
who are gonna go, "Well, I actually can do
a better job if I'm open." My, my constituency,

00:20:18.460 --> 00:20:25.140
my audience, my patients, you know, whoever
the people are that I work with, um, my community

